<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING 1994-1995 DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60 DDEC III ENGINES - DIAGNOSTICS AND TROUBLESHOOTING -
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL (APS/IVS)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ACCELERATOR PEDAL (APS/IVS)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Review the circuit diagram and inspect the TPS circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08051_115.xml" xrefid="hl08058bt">Before Troubleshooting</hotlnk>. The following
                tests (Tests 1, 2 &#38; 3) check the (APS/IVS) connection and related International cab and engine
                harness connections leading to the ECM.
            </para>
            <para>The tests should be performed if a DDEC III fault code indicates a problem in the circuits or if the
                Prolink indicates that the APS/IVS is not working properly while monitoring switches.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Tests 1.3.3.1 through 1.3.3.3 must be performed in sequence.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Accelerator Position Sensor (APS)</title>
            <para>This test checks the APS circuits in the accelerator pedal assembly. This test will identify if the
                resistance of the pedal circuits is within specifications.
            </para>
            <table id="t0805803" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 1 - Testing Accelerator Position Sensor (APS)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING ACCELERATOR POSITION SENSOR (APS)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect the accelerator pedal from cab harness connector (267). At the pedal
                                    side of (267) measure resistance between terminals A and C with the pedal in the
                                    idle position, then with the pedal fully depressed. Resistance should be 2000 to
                                    3000 ohms in all positions.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal A to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2000 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With the pedal at idle, at connector (267) measure resistance between terminals B
                                    and C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1500 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With pedal at full throttle position, at connector (267) measure resistance
                                    between terminals B and C. Resistance must be 1000 ohms less than reading at idle
                                    position and must be 250 to 1500 ohms.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>250 to 1500 ohms, and 1000 less than idle position reading.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal, measure resistance to the metal part of pedal assembly and
                                    terminals A, B, C, D and E.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Accelerator pedal metal to terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>APS sensor checks good. Go to Test 2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</title>
            <para>Perform Test 1 before performing this test. This test checks the IVS circuits in the accelerator pedal
                assembly.
            </para>
            <table id="t0805805" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 2 - Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING IDLE VALIDATION SWITCH (IVS)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With accelerator pedal still disconnected at connector (267) and the pedal at
                                    idle, measure resistance between terminal F and E on the accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal F to E.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;125 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (267), measure resistance between terminals E and F while slowly
                                    depressing the pedal (idle to full throttle). After approximately 10&#176; of travel
                                    the resistance should be 100K ohms or more.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At accelerator pedal E to F. after 10&#176; of travel.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace APS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The APS and IVS functions check good. Note: this test is not able to check the
                                    timing function between the two functions.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Test 3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Accelerator Pedal (APS/IVS) Circuits</title>
            <para>Inspect APS/IVS circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08051_115.xml" xrefid="hl08058bt">Before Troubleshooting</hotlnk>. This test checks
                the cab and engine harness APS/IVS circuits for opens, shorts to ground, shorts to "hot" circuits and
                shorts to other circuits in the harness and checks the circuits for continuity. Refer to circuit diagram
                on previous page.
                <emph type="bold">Perform tests 1 and 2 before performing this test.</emph>
            </para>
            <table id="t0805806" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 3 - Testing Accelerator Pedal (APS/IVS) Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <thead valign="bottom">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING ACCELERATOR PEDAL (APS/IVS) CIRCUITS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With accelerator pedal disconnected from the cab harness at (267), disconnect
                                    connector (273) from the ECM. At International ECM connector (273), measure
                                    resistance to gnd. at terminals E1, C3, D2 and A3.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>E1, C3, D2 and A3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to gnd in circuit where resistance at terminal is less than 100K
                                    ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) measure resistance between terminals E1, C3, D2, A3 and all
                                    other terminals in connector (273).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>E1, C3, D2 and A3 to each other.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short between circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                    ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) measure voltage to gnd. at terminals E1, C3, D2, A3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>E1, C3, D2 and A3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 volt.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to unwanted voltage source in circuit with more than 1V, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (267) measure resistance to gnd. at terminal F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(267) F to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in gnd. path between connector (267) terminal F and
                                    negative battery terminal, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) use test lead to jumper terminal E1 to negative battery
                                    terminal. At connector (267) measure resistance between terminals E and F.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(267) E to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99B between connectors (273) and (267),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) use test lead to jumper terminal C3 to negative battery
                                    terminal. At connector (267) measure resistance between terminals A and F.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(267) A to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99-R between connectors (273) and (267),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) use test lead to jumper terminal D2 to negative battery
                                    terminal. At connector (267) measure resistance between terminals B and F.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(267) B to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99 between connectors (273) and (267),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (273) use test lead to jumper terminal A3 to negative battery
                                    terminal. At connector (267) measure resistance between terminals C and F.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(267) C to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>APS/IVS circuits between (273) and (267) check good</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99A between connectors (273) and (267),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
